                     </font>
                     <padding>
                        <Insets left="50.0" />
                     </padding>
                  </TextArea>
                  <Label styleClass="label-text" text="Test Microphone" />
                  <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="114.0" prefWidth="800.0" text="This screen is used to test the level of your microphone. Make sure to test it if this&#10;is the first time that you have used name sayer&#10;&#10;Back To Main Menu Button - Go back to main menu">
                     <padding>
                        <Insets left="50.0" />
                     </padding></TextArea>
                  <Label styleClass="label-text" text="Name Selection" />
                  <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="310.0" prefWidth="800.0" text="This is where you select the names that you'd like to practice. First, you can see &#10;two lists. The left one includes all of the available names from the database.&#10;The right list includes the names that have been selected for practicing.&#10;&#10;You can search the name that by typing into the search text box. This will filter&#10;the list on the left side.&#10;&#10;There are 3 ways that you can add a name to practice:&#10;&#10;1. Add Custom Name Button - This is where you can add the concatenation of the&#10;                                                Names from the database. For example, you can &#10;                                                write &quot;Catherine Watson&quot;. This allows you to add full&#10;                                                names to practice, made of first and last &#10;                                                names from the database&#10;&#10;2. Select from the database list - You can also select the names that you'd like to&#10;                                                   practice from the list on the left side. Click on a&#10;                                                   name, and press the &quot;&gt;&gt;&quot; button, which moves &#10;                                                   the selected name to the practice list.&#10;&#10;3. Import a text file - If you have a text file with a list of names, you can also &#10;                                 import the text file by pressing the &quot;import a text file&quot; button.&#10;                                 Each line in your text file should be a different name&#10;&#10;&quot;&lt;&lt;&quot; Button - If you have made a mistake, you can de-select the name from the &#10;                       list of names that you want to practice.&#10;&#10;&quot;Start Practicing&quot; Button - Once you are satisfied with your practice list, you can &#10;                                        press this button. This will take you to the next screen,&#10;                                        where you can start practicing the names that you have&#10;                                        selected. &#10;&#10;If mutliple names have been selected, the program will ask you if you would like&#10;to randomize the order of your list. If this is what you'd like, then press &quot;OK&quot;&#10;                             ">
                     <padding>
                        <Insets left="50.0" />
                     </padding></TextArea>
                  <Label styleClass="label-text" text="Playing Names" />
                  <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="306.0" prefWidth="871.0" text="This is where you can begin practicing the names that you have previously selected. On &#10;the left side, you can see the list of names that you have selected. You can scroll through &#10;the list using the mouse wheel.&#10;&#10;You can navigate through this list by pressing 'Previous Name' and 'Next Name' buttons.&#10;&#10;'Play' Button - This button will play the recording of the name from the database&#10;&#10;'Record' Button - This button will take you to the recording screen, where you can record&#10;                          your pronunciation of the current name&#10;&#10;'Past Recordings' Button - This button will take you to the past recordings screen, where&#10;                                         you can play and review all of your past recordings, as well as&#10;                                         the database recordings (there may be mutliple database &#10;                                         recordings&#10;&#10;'Toggle Quality' Button - This button is used to mark the quality of the database recording.&#10;                                       If the recording is poor, mark it as poor.&#10;" />
                  <Label styleClass="label-text" text="Recording" />
                  <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="200.0" prefWidth="200.0" text="This is where you will record your own pronunciations of the name that you have selected.&#10;The 'Play Your Recording' and 'Save' buttons will be disabled until you make a recording&#10;&#10;'Start Recording' Button - This button will start recording your microphone. The recording&#10;                                         will  last at most 20 seconds to give you enough time to say &#10;                                         the name. Once pressed, this button will turn into the &#10;                                         'Stop Recording' Button&#10;&#10;'Stop Button' - This button will appear once the 'Start Button' is pressed. This will stop the &#10;                        recording of your microphone. It should be pressed once you are done &#10;                         saying the name to reduce the amount of silence in the recording&#10;&#10;'Play Example' Button - This will play the database recording of the name&#10;&#10;'Play Your Recording' - This button will play the recording that you have just made back&#10;                                      to you. If you are not satisfied with the recording, simply &#10;                                      press 'Record' again or press 'Back' and press 'Ok' when the &#10;                                      confirmation pops up.&#10;&#10;'Save' - This button saves your latest unsaved recording " />
                  <Label styleClass="label-text" text="Past Recordings" />
                  <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="200.0" prefWidth="200.0" text="This is where you can see all of your past recordings that you've recorded. You can &#10;also see the all of the database recordings for the name. You will see a list on your &#10;left, which will either dispaly the database recordings, or the user recordings&#10; (A label will be on top of it, indicating which list it currently is displaying&#10;&#10;'Play Selected' Button - This button will play the currently selected recording&#10;&#10;'Play From Database' Button - This button will play the main recording from the database&#10;&#10;'View Database' Button - This will show the database recordings list in the list on the left&#10;&#10;'View User' Button - This will show the user recordings list in the list on the left" />
